cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with recommendation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a user-sensitive ensemble method, which involves clustering users and multi-task learning, both of which are techniques commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on real-world datasets, which falls under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
